General State Class Idea:
    1) One idea I had for refactoring the enemy classes was creating a base active and
        passive state class which would be inherited by any further state classes that
        are to be implemented. This would allow for further interactability with items
        such as poison or boss types. For example the damaged enemy and dead enemy
        state would be related to the passive state. In a similar vein, I think the
        player states could also benefit from this, as it would allow that extra ease of
        customizability without worrying about duplicate code.